  "candidate_text": "Tessa runs her thumb along the fold of the program, pressing the crease sharper, and she finds herself composing the explanation in her head \u2014 not for Eli, not yet, but for the version of herself that needs to hear it first: a toast is a single clean arc, and you don't interrupt an arc with footnotes, you don't slow the room down with shared credit when the room needs to move. The phone screen has gone dark in her other hand and she lets it stay dark, because opening it now would mean the explanation hasn't finished forming, and she needs it finished before she speaks. Through the coatroom door she can still hear the donor room converting \u2014 chairs scraping, voices warming back toward ordinary \u2014 and she understands that the moment is already becoming the version people will carry home, which means she is not too late, which means what she did was a kind of timing, not a kind of taking.",
